Subject: [PATCH 1932/2508] ASoC: topology: copying enum text values

commit 0f75ad233ef2ab6d041dd4c0ab705179beb66aae from
https://github.com/01org/linux-apollolake-i

Default info function for the enumerated double mixer
requires text values. Else this can cause a NULL pointer
exception.

To avoid this, the texts field of structure soc_enum
has been updated with the correct pointer to the
texts.

Change-Id: I7f1fb5c11128b2857d4cd9ba3e4f2c2e0b2a92b5
Signed-off-by: Mousumi Jana <mousumix.jana@intel.com>
---
 sound/soc/soc-topology.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/soc-topology.c b/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
index a697f9f..98b5d37 100644
--- a/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
+++ b/sound/soc/soc-topology.c
@@ -876,6 +876,8 @@ static int soc_tplg_denum_create_texts(struct soc_enum *se,
 		}
 	}
 
+	se->texts = se->dobj.control.dtexts;
+
 	return 0;
 
